                                                            <div class="panel-body toggle-content post-content"><p><strong>April 30, 2018</strong></p>
                                                                <p>
                                                                    <img class="alignnone wp-image-12450 size-full" src="https://microfin360.com/web/wp-content/uploads/2018/05/500.png" alt="" width="800" height="600" srcset="https://microfin360.com/web/wp-content/uploads/2018/05/500-200x150.png 200w, https://microfin360.com/web/wp-content/uploads/2018/05/500-300x225.png 300w, https://microfin360.com/web/wp-content/uploads/2018/05/500-400x300.png 400w, https://microfin360.com/web/wp-content/uploads/2018/05/500-600x450.png 600w, https://microfin360.com/web/wp-content/uploads/2018/05/500-768x576.png 768w, https://microfin360.com/web/wp-content/uploads/2018/05/500.png 800w" sizes="(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px" /></p>
                                                                <p>DataSoft Systems Bangladesh Ltd signed a contract  with Natahan Associates on 1st April 2018 to provide business analysis service for preparation of Microfinance Credit Information Bureau (MF-CIB) Database, under BFP- B project funded by DFID. Microcredit Regulatory Authority (MRA) will execute, implement & maintain MF-CIB with the assistance of Bangladesh Bank. As part of the project a business requirement collection workshop held on April 30, 2018 at RRF, Jashore.</p>
